In this report:
[1] Regional alert
[2] Yellow fever in Pindorama and Ibirá

******
[1] Regional alert
Date: Tue 1 Nov 2016
Source: UOL Notícias [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://noticias.uol.com.br/ultimas-noticias/agencia-estado/2016/11/01/risco-de-febre-amarela-poe-em-alerta-regiao-de-rio-preto.htm


Yellow fever puts the [São José do] Rio Preto region on alert
-------------------------------------------------------------
People who need to go to the São José do Rio Preto region, in the north of São Paulo state, must be vaccinated against yellow fever. The alert, by the Epidemiological Surveillance Group (GVE) of the state Secretariat of Health, is issued on account of a series of deaths of monkeys after contracting the disease in municipalities of the region.

According to the Rio Preto GVE Deputy Director, Monica Regina Bocchi, of the 4 dead monkey cases, 2 now have been definitely confirmed as yellow fever and the other 2 have been positive in the initial tests, are awaiting results of [further] tests. "The problem is that we have not been able to test them in many cases. What is worrisome is that we have nearly 40 suspected [yellow fever] deaths [in monkeys] in the region." In all these instances, there has been action to block [human cases] with vaccination of the surrounding population as well as vector control, especially of forest mosquitoes.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
